# User-facing text in Spanish

Any text rendered to the user in the frontend must be written in **Spanish**.

This includes:

- Visible labels, buttons, titles, and headings.
- Placeholders, tooltips, and helper text.
- Validation, error, and success messages (toasts, alerts, notifications).
- Empty states and loading text.

Keep code identifiers (variables, props, functions, component names) in English — only the text shown to the user must be in Spanish.

## Example

```vue
<!-- ❌ AVOID: user-facing text in English -->
<template>
  <UButton :loading="isSaving">Save changes</UButton>
  <UInput placeholder="Search..." />
</template>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT: user-facing text in Spanish -->
<template>
  <UButton :loading="isSaving">Guardar cambios</UButton>
  <UInput placeholder="Buscar..." />
</template>
```
